<PolicyLayout title="Donation Disclaimer" lastReviewed="July 2025">

<p>
  Thank you for considering supporting Hope For Families. This page explains how donations are used, our
  commitment to financial transparency, and important information about making a gift.
</p>

<h2>1. How Donations Are Used</h2>
<p>
  Every donation made to Hope For Families directly supports our charitable mission: building stronger families,
  empowered communities and brighter futures for African and ethnic-minority families across Scotland.
</p>
<p>Funds are used across our core programmes, which include:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Little Stars Initiative</strong> — STEM Club, fun outings and developmental activities for children aged 5–12.</li>
  <li><strong>Adolescent Development Initiative</strong> — life skills, mentoring, creativity and employability training for young people aged 13–17.</li>
  <li><strong>Community Mental Health &amp; Wellbeing</strong> — Afro Dance Exercise, Cozy Corner social sessions and peer support.</li>
  <li><strong>FirstPass Football Academy</strong> — weekly football training building teamwork, discipline and confidence.</li>
  <li><strong>Food Bank &amp; Café</strong> — weekly community meals for families and individuals facing food insecurity or isolation.</li>
  <li><strong>Operational costs</strong> — a portion of donations may be used to cover essential running costs such as venue hire, insurance, administration and staff costs that enable all programmes to function.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  Hope For Families does not pay trustees for their governance role. Operational staff costs are kept to a
  minimum and are disclosed in our annual accounts submitted to OSCR.
</p>

<h2>2. Gift Aid</h2>
<p>
  If you are a UK taxpayer, please consider making your donation Gift Aid-eligible. Gift Aid allows us to
  reclaim 25p from HMRC for every £1 you donate at no extra cost to you. To be eligible, the amount of
  Income Tax and/or Capital Gains Tax you pay for the current tax year must be at least equal to the amount
  of Gift Aid all charities claim on your donations.
</p>
<p>
  When you make a Gift Aid declaration, your personal details are shared with HMRC solely to process the claim.
  This is a legal requirement and is covered by our <a href="/policies/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a>.
</p>

<h2>3. Donation Processing</h2>
<p>
  Online donations are processed through <strong>JustGiving</strong>, a regulated payment platform. We do not
  store your payment card details. JustGiving's own privacy policy governs how they handle your payment
  information.
</p>

<h2>4. Refund Policy</h2>
<p>
  Donations to Hope For Families are voluntary gifts made in support of our charitable work. As such, we are
  generally unable to offer refunds once a donation has been made and allocated. If you believe a donation was
  made in error, please contact us at <a href="mailto:kelechioliora@gmail.com">kelechioliora@gmail.com</a>
  within 14 days and we will review your request.
</p>

<h2>5. Financial Accountability</h2>
<p>
  As a registered Scottish charity, Hope For Families is regulated by the Office of the Scottish Charity
  Regulator (OSCR) under charity number <strong>SC053715</strong>. We are required to:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Submit annual accounts and an annual return to OSCR.</li>
  <li>Operate in accordance with our governing document and charitable purposes.</li>
  <li>Use charitable funds only in the pursuit of our charitable objectives.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  Our accounts are publicly available through the OSCR charity register at
  <a href="https://www.oscr.org.uk/about-charities/search-the-register/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">oscr.org.uk</a>.
</p>

<h2>6. Contact</h2>
